OL,7,FThe award-winning writer was praised
OL,8,Fby the Swedish Academy for the
OL,9,F"uncompromising and compassionate
OL,10,Fpenetration of the effects of
OL,11,Fcolonialism" reflected in his 10
OL,12,Fnovels including Memory of Departure,
OL,13,FParadise and By The Sea.
OL,15,FGurnah arrived in Britain in the 1960s
OL,16,Fafter persuading his father to let him
OL,17,Fand his brother travel out of the
OL,18,Fcountry through "illegal" means,
OL,19,Falthough they did not tell their
OL,20,Fmother they were leaving.
