OL,4,Cliterature A-level as it did not feel
OL,5,C'useful'
OL,7,FHe said: "It was difficult to organise
OL,8,Fbecause it was not possible to have
OL,9,Ftravel documents. The security
OL,10,Fadvisers for the government were from
OL,11,Fthe GDR, East Germany, and they were,
OL,12,Fas you know, obsessed with making sure
OL,13,Fpeople don't travel, don't leave, so
OL,14,Fit meant that we had to leave in
OL,15,Frather, well, really rather illegal
OL,16,Fways, which I'll leave at that.
OL,18,FSpeaking about whether he got his
OL,19,Fmother's blessing to leave, he said:
OL,20,F"No, we couldn't tell her.
